name: Alain Delon
summary: French cinema icon Alain Delon, known for his smoldering good looks and captivating performances, has passed away at the age of 88. The actor, hailed as a "cinematic heartthrob" and "French monument," left an indelible mark on the silver screen, particularly in films such as "Le Samourai." Delon's life was intertwined with both fame and controversy, as he was both adored by fans and embroiled in scandals involving women and alleged gun ownership. Despite these complexities, Delon's enduring legacy as a cinematic icon remains unchallenged, with his image forever etched in the hearts of film enthusiasts worldwide.

name: Rodanthe house collapses
summary: Along the Outer Banks, Hurricane Ernesto triggered severe consequences, causing the collapse of a house in Cape Hatteras, leading to coastal area closures in Rodanthe. Another home has succumbed to the ocean's relentless forces, a stark reminder of the escalating impacts of climate change. A video captured the dramatic moment of a house disintegrating into the sea, marking the seventh such incident in the past four years. Despite clean-up efforts, the collapsed house in Rodanthe continues to break apart, leaving the Seashore beach with its seventh house lost to the ocean's fury.

name: Full moon
summary: In August 2024, a rare celestial event will occur: a super blue moon. As the name suggests, this full moon will be larger and brighter than usual, as it will be close to its closest point to Earth (a supermoon) and will be the second full moon in a calendar month (a blue moon). This particular super blue moon is even more uncommon, as it will be one of four consecutive supermoons and is expected to be one of the largest and brightest of the year. Hence, it is anticipated to be a captivating sight for stargazers and astronomy enthusiasts alike.
